\N<Man>Segi-san, where do you think you're going? I hate to think
it, but if you're planning to go to the ruins ahead, I'd
advise against it.

\N<Man>The entrance management of the ruins that have been in this
town for ages is now being handled by Ryuda's soldiers...

\N<Man>There are still some layers of resistance against Ryuda's
soldiers in the city, which is quite a nuisance. I keep
saying we should avoid pointless conflicts...

\N<Man>Armor to protect oneself can be said to be the bare minimum
preparation. Whether exploring ruins or fighting in the
training grounds.

\N<Hojiko>Don't make such a face. It's not like I was waiting here for
you or anything.

\N<Hojiko>Although... if you were to come see me on your own, I'd
always be delighted... hehe.

\N<Hojiko>Actually, it seems that guy from my place is around here
again. Really, I can understand men wanting someone like
Segi-san, but I can't believe there are men who would bother
with a woman like him.

\N<Hojiko>Well, I have you, Segi-san... How about tonight? I'll make
sure you're satisfied... hehe.

\N<Segi>...The arena is in the opposite direction.

\N<Segi>Actually, I saw the request board at the management
office... Rozaro-san's request board.

\N<Rozaro>Request board? Ah, you mean the sparring partner thing. What
about it?

\N<Segi>...Well, I was wondering if I might not be of any help to
you?

\N<Segi>Yes, I am aware that I might not be strong enough to be your
sparring partner.

\N<Segi>But you have always been a great help to me and my son, and
more than anything, it would serve as training for myself as
well.

\N<Segi>I know it's selfish of me to offer to help with training
when in the end, it's for my own benefit.
\N<Segi>But... what do you think? Can I be of any help to you?

\N<Rozaro>...Understood. Then I'll accept your offer without
reservation.
\N<Segi>Really? Thank you so much. I'll do my very best.

\N<Rozaro>Of course, I'll pay you for your time as a training partner.
But since it's training, I can't hold back. Is that alright
with you?

\N<Rozaro>Hmm, then let's begin in the forest outskirts as soon as
you're ready.
\N<Rozaro>Then, Segi-san, shall we start the training immediately?

\N<Rozaro>...Segi-san, don't overdo it. You should rest a bit. You
can't handle me all at once.
\N<Segi>No, I'm fine... What should I... help with next...

\N<Rozaro>...I appreciate the sentiment. But if we've managed to find
this time, I want it to be meaningful for you too.

\N<Rozaro>In other words... this training should be beneficial for you
as well as for me.

\N<Rozaro>So from here on out, let's focus on training for your sake.
Consider it part of my request to you, is that okay?

\N<Rozaro>Don't thank me just yet. Of course, I'll take it seriously
since I'm involved. Make sure you don't regret agreeing to
train with me.

\N<Rozaro>Hmm... Listen, Segi-san. As a warrior, there are several key
elements you're critically lacking.

\N<Rozaro>One is muscular strength, which is the source of power in
attacks. Another is physical strength, which is essential
for defense against attacks. And one more is vitality, the
source of life.

\N<Rozaro>All are important elements in battle. Now, what do you
consider important? I'll accompany you in any training you
wish to focus on.

\N<Segi>(Indeed, all the elements Rozaro-san mentioned seem
important... Which one should I choose...)

\N<Rozaro>You're focusing on muscular strength. Understood. Then let's
proceed with today's training in that manner.

\N<Rozaro>Ah, it was good training for me too. And I plan to keep
posting requests at the management office regularly from now
on.

\N<Rozaro>If you feel like it, please call on me again. I'm always
ready to assist you.
\N<Segi>Yes. I'll be looking forward to it next time as well.
